==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catalpa
<hw>Ca*tal"pa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the language
of the Indians of Carolina, where Catesby discovered this tree in the
year 1726.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of American and East
Indian trees, of which the best known species are the <spn>Catalpa
bignonioides</spn>, a large, ornamental North American tree, with
spotted white flowers and long cylindrical pods, and the <spn>Catalpa
speciosa</spn>, of the Mississipi valley; -- called also <altname>Indian
bean</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>catalufa</ent>⟦br⟧
